    <div id="about" class="info">
      <div id="fb-root"></div>
      <% if @login_redirect %>
        <input type="hidden" id="login_redirect" value="<%= @login_redirect %>" />
      <% end %>
      <div class="header">
        <h2>Civic Art</h2>
        <ul class="nav">
          <li class="selected"><a href="for-artists">For Artists</a></li>
          <li><a href="for-voters">For Voters</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <div class="about_border">
           <div class="left">
             <div id="for-artists" class="slide selected">
               <p>OurCommonPlace <%= @community.name %> is proud to announce <%= @community.name %>'s first ever Civic Art Contest! We created the Civic Art Contest as a fun and engaging way for the students of <%= @community.name %>'s public schools to show off their skills and community spirit at the same time. Create a work of art that shows your civic pride or answers the question: "Why do you love <%= @community.name %>?".</p>
               <p><strong>How it works:</strong></p>
               <p>
                 1. Create a work of art (any medium!) that shows your <%= @community.name %> pride
                 <br>
                 2. Submit your art by <strong>March 24th</strong> to <a href="mailto:ricky@ourcommonplace.com">ricky@ourcommonplace.com</a>
                 <br>
                 3. Have your friends, family, and neighbors in town vote for your artwork on OurCommonPlace <%= @community.name %> for a chance to win a $100 cash prize, the Civic Art Award, and a cool t-shirt!
               </p>
               <p><strong>Rules:</strong></p>
               <ul class="neighborhood_list">
                 <li>Any and all mediums accepted! Anythings from pencil drawings to paintings to videos or songs! Be creative! We'd love to see some outside-the-box entries.</li>
                 <li>You must be of high school age or younger to enter.</li>
                 <li>All voting will take place on <a href="<%= @community.links.base %>/pages/<%= @community.slug %>civicart">www.<%= @community.slug %>.OurCommonPlace.com</a></li>
                 <li>Voting closes on <strong>March 29th</strong> and all votes will be counted in the following days. The entry with the most votes wins!</li>
               </ul>
             </div>
             <div id="for-voters" class="slide">
               <p>Support local students! Vote for your favorite pieces of 'Civic Art' in <%= @community.name %>'s first ever Civic Art Contest sponsored by OurCommonPlace <%= @community.name %>! </p>
               <p><strong>To view contest entries:</strong></p>
               <p>
               1. Head over to <a href="<%= @community.links.base %>/pages/<%= @community.slug %>civicart">www.<%= @community.slug %>.OurCommonPlace.com</a>
                 <br>
                 2. If you're not already a member, sign up (it's 100% free!) using your real first and last name. 
                 <br>
                 3. Click the '<%= @community.name %> Civic Art' page and browse the artist's entries that have been posted. Check back every day for new posts!
                 </p>
               <p><strong>To Vote:</strong></p>
               <p>
                 1. Click the 'Thank' button located on the posting of your favorite pieces of art. Vote for as many entries as you'd like!
                 <br>
                 2. Share the post with as many people as you can to ensure the art that you voted for is the winner!
               </p>
               <p>Voting ends on <strong>March 29th</strong>, be sure to get your votes in before then!</p>
             </div>
           </div>
